		</tr>
	</table><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">X-Treme Promotions Presents the 2026 NATURAL BC CUP.</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>This year's event is set to take centre stage on Saturday May 16th at the Rotary Centre theatre in Kelowna, BC . This high-energy event will bring together the finest natural athletes from across Canada to display their dedication, discipline, and sculpted physiques.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>With its reputation as a premier natural event, the Natural BC CUP promises an unforgettable experience for both participants and spectators. The show aims to celebrate the artistry and athleticism of bodybuilding, as competitors showcase their years of training, commitment, and passion for the sport.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>The BC CUP will feature multiple categories, including Men's Bodybuilding, Women's Physique, Classic Physique, Figure, Wellness and Bikini. Contestants will be judged on their muscularity, symmetry, stage presence, and overall presentation, making it an exhilarating visual spectacle for enthusiasts and novices alike.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>This year's event boasts a panel of distinguished judges, composed of industry experts and IFBB Pro athletes, who will bring their extensive knowledge and expertise to ensure fair and impartial evaluations. The judging process will be conducted with the utmost professionalism and transparency, ensuring that the deserving champions are recognized for their extraordinary dedication and hard work.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>In addition to the competitive aspect, the BC CUP  will also provide an opportunity for attendees to immerse themselves in the vibrant bodybuilding community. Industry-leading vendors and sponsors will be present in the Lobby, offering a wide range of products and services tailored to fitness enthusiasts and professionals alike.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>\"We are thrilled to bring the BC CUP back for another spectacular year,\" said Dean Brandt , CEO of Xtreme Promotions. \"This event is not just about showcasing incredible natural physiques; it's about celebrating the spirit of commitment, dedication, and personal growth that embodies the bodybuilding community. We invite everyone to witness the sheer power and beauty that unfolds on stage.\"<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Tickets for the BC CUP are now available for purchase through the Rotary Box Office. Early booking is recommended as this event attracts a large audience and has sold out the last 2 years.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>For further information, please visit the promoters website at <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://xtremepromotions.org\">xtremepromotions.org.</a><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><h2>Pricing</h2><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Morning Event <span><br/></span>Regular - $54.46</span>  ($45.00 base price + $2.36 CIF + $7.10 service charge)<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Senior - $49.86</span>  ($41.00 base price + $2.36 CIF + $6.50 service charge)<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Evening Event<span><br/></span>Regular - $70.56</span>  ($59.00 base price + $2.36 CIF + $9.20 service charge)<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Senior - $63.66</span>  ($53.00 base price + $2.36 CIF + $8.30 service charge)<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">All above prices are CAD and include GST.</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>---<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">Mary Irwin Theatre at the Rotary Centre for the Arts event tickets include a $2.36 Capital Improvement Fee (CIF). A service fee is added for box office costs, card processing, and taxes. <span class=\"BoldText\">2026 BC Cup</span> tickets and their applicable fees are non-refundable.</span><span><br/></span>
""";
