  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Bored Teachers";
  schema:description """
	<table class=\" BorderOn\">
		<tr>
			<td align=\"left\" colspan=\"1\"><img src=\"https://system.spektrix.com/kelownacommunitytheatre/files/2f70858f-d7c4-4054-8847-1213bee77e88.jpg\" /> </td><td align=\"left\"><h2>Outback presents </h2><h1><span class=\"UnderlineText\">BORED TEACHERS:</span></h1><h2>\"IS IT FRIDAY YET?!\" COMEDY TOUR - 2026</h2></td>
		</tr>
	</table><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Warning</span>- May contain PG-13 language, teacher truths, and uncontrollable fits of laughter. <span><br/></span>---<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>They’ve graded the papers, survived the staff meetings, and lost their last ounce of patience… and now they’re taking it out on stage! <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Bored Teachers is BACK with brand-new jokes, bigger laughs, and the most relatable teacher comedy you’ll ever hear. For nearly a decade, Bored Teachers has been the #1 voice of teacher humor—racking up <span class=\"BoldText\">over 1 billion views</span>, amassing <span class=\"BoldText\">10 million+ followers</span>, and hosting the <span class=\"BoldText\">#1 teacher-comedy podcast</span> on the planet. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Since 2022, they’ve performed for <span class=\"BoldText\">200,000+ teachers worldwide</span>, and sold out <span class=\"BoldText\">200+ theaters across 49 states, 5 countries, and 3 continents.</span> Their BRAND NEW “Is It Friday Yet?!” Tour starting January 2026 is more than a comedy show—it’s the ultimate night of laughter and solidarity for anyone who’s ever worked in education, taught a lesson, or just survived parent-teacher conferences. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Get ready to laugh until you cry as the funniest teacher-comedians in the world share their side-splitting stories, savage truths, and hilarious classroom confessions. Whether you’re a teacher, a parent, or just someone who’s been in school, this show will have you nodding, clapping, and hollering, “That’s SO TRUE!” <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>---<span><br/></span><h2>Pricing</h2><span class=\"BoldText\">Platinum seating  $117.07</span>  ($99.75 base price + $2.36 CIF + $14.96 service charge)<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Tier 1  $82.57</span>  ($69.75 base price + $2.36 CIF + $10.46 service charge)<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Tier 1 Aisle  $94.07</span>  ($79.75 base price + $2.36 CIF + $11.96 service charge)<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Tier 2  $71.07</span>  ($59.75 base price + $2.36 CIF + $8.96 service charge)<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Tier 2 Aisle  $82.57</span>  ($69.75 base price + $2.36 CIF + $10.46 service charge)<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Tier 3  $54.97</span>  ($45.75 base price + $2.36 CIF + $6.86 service charge)<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Tier 3 Aisle  $66.47</span>  ($55.75 base price + $2.36 CIF + $8.36 service charge)<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">All above prices are in CAD and include GST.</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>---<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">Kelowna Community Theatre event tickets include a $2.25 Capital Improvement Fee (CIF) and 5% GST. A service fee is added for box office costs, card processing, and taxes. Tickets for <span class=\"BoldText\">Bored Teachers</span> and their applicable service fees are non-refundable.</span>
""";
