<http://www.spektrix.com/kelownacommunitytheatre/event/257602AHGDTKHDSBSJGRMGPKPHNGVHMRV>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "RCA Presents - Ché Aimee Dorval ";
  schema:description """
	<table class=\" BorderOn\">
		<tr>
			<td align=\"left\" colspan=\"1\"><img src=\"https://system.spektrix.com/kelownacommunitytheatre/files/35fdd583-4a46-4008-82f1-f3334ccd1a5e.jpg\" /> </td><td align=\"left\"><h2>Rotary Centre for the Arts presents </h2><h1><span class=\"UnderlineText\">CHÉ AIMEE DORVAL</span></h1></td>
		</tr>
	</table><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Canadian artist Ché Aimee Dorval offers a sonic escape—an immersive cinematic journey where late-night trip-hop, airy dream pop, and laid-back electronica drift together with a touch of alt-indie edge. With sleek production reminiscent of Goldfrapp, Bonobo's organic pulse, and Lana Del Rey's moody allure, Ché crafts a soundtrack for those chasing city lights and after-hours reveries. Step into her world, where every beat paints a scene and every melody tells a story. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>In 2023, Ché was featured on a haunting duet with Gord Downie (The Tragically Hip) and made guest appearances on Devin Townsend's Lightwork, setting the stage for her third solo album, The Crowned, co-produced by Bob Rock (Metallica). Clash Magazine praised the record for “fusing pop, soul, and indie elements to produce something potent and original,” while Knotfest called the standout track “Falling Under” a “timeless earworm.” <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Fresh off a busy year of touring in 2024 to support The Crowned, Ché channeled her passion for alt-pop and synthwave into a new body of work that promises to push her signature sound even further. This spring, she’ll release new material that marks the next step in her ongoing evolution as an artist. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://www.cheaimeedorval.com/\">For more information, CLICK HERE</a><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><h2>Pricing</h2><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Regular: $35.00</span> ($28.38 + $2.36 CIF + $4.26 Service Fee)<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">30 under 30: $25.67</span> ($20.27 + $2.36 CIF + $3.04 Service Fee)<span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">All above prices include GST.</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>---<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">Mary Irwin Theatre at the Rotary Centre for the Arts event tickets include a $2.36 Capital Improvement Fee (CIF). A service fee is added for box office costs, card processing, and taxes. <span class=\"BoldText\">Ché Aimee Dorval</span> tickets and their applicable fees are non-refundable.</span><span><br/></span>
""";
