<http://www.spektrix.com/kelownacommunitytheatre/event/382001ADHJTKSPDTVCNSNBJBPVDRHVNPS>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "RCA Presents - Patti Savard - A Life in Transition";
  schema:description """
	<table class=\" BorderOn\">
		<tr>
			<td align=\"left\" colspan=\"1\"><img /> </td><td align=\"left\"><h2>Rotary Centre for the Arts presents </h2><h1><span class=\"UnderlineText\">PATTI SAVARD - A LIFE IN TRANSITION</span></h1><h2><span class=\"ItalicText\"><span class=\"BoldText\">with special guest Michael V. Smith</span></span></h2></td>
		</tr>
	</table><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">Life in Transition</span> is a bold, hilarious one-woman show following Patti Savard, a trans woman turning life’s challenges into laughter. Through stand-up, storytelling, theatrics, and song, she unpacks growing up in the 80’s and 90’s, navigating a world that didn’t yet make space for her true self. With razor-sharp wit and unapologetic honesty, Patti explores identity, gender roles, and belonging. From awkward teen moments to the triumphs of living authentically, no laugh is unearned. Brace yourself for a queer-infused rollercoaster of humour, heart, and the gay agenda you didn’t know you needed! <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>To learn more about Patti Savard, visit <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://www.instagram.com/pattisavard18/\">here.</a><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Genderqueer, sassy, and cute as all get-out, Michael V. Smith doesn't fit his square peg into round boxes. His brand of improv and audience play has made him a hosting sensation for thirty years. From Pony the Queer Cabaret and Art on the Line, to the Vancouver Comedy Festival and queer events across the country and beyond, Smith rocks the room awake with the live moment.  <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>To learn more about Michael V. Smith, visit <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://www.michaelvsmith.com\">michaelvsmith.com.</a> <span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>---<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><h2>Pricing</h2><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Adult  $38.94</span>  ($31.50 base price + $2.36 CIF + $5.08 service charge)<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Student w/ID  $26.86</span>  ($21.00 base price + $2.36 CIF + $3.50 service charge)<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">All above prices include GST.</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>---<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">Mary Irwin Theatre at the Rotary Centre for the Arts event tickets include a $2.36 Capital Improvement Fee (CIF). A service fee is added for box office costs, card processing, and taxes. <span class=\"BoldText\">Patti Savard - A Life in Transition</span> tickets and their applicable fees are non-refundable.</span><span><br/></span>
""";
  schema:startDate "2026-11-04T19:30:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
