<http://www.spektrix.com/kelownacommunitytheatre/event/379601AQSLLBRDDBGHNTGMVCGCJQMCRQG>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "RCA Presents Kenny \"Blues Boss\" Wayne";
  schema:description """
	<table class=\" BorderOn\">
		<tr>
			<td align=\"left\" colspan=\"1\"><img src=\"https://system.spektrix.com/kelownacommunitytheatre/files/950046cd-d3d2-4310-adac-af9cff922335.jpg\" /> </td><td align=\"left\"><h2>Rotary Centre for the Arts presents </h2><h1><span class=\"UnderlineText\">KENNY \"BLUES BOSS\" WAYNE</span></h1></td>
		</tr>
	</table><span><br/></span>This high energy show will take you on a journey back to a time when piano players ruled in Texarkana, New Orleans, St. Louis, Chicago and Kansas City with classic barrelhouse boogie piano. The sound of the piano could be heard in just about every juke joint throughout the Southern states. It all originated in Southern gospel churches, where the shouting of the choir filled the room, singing old-time religious songs led by the choir director, with the piano player driving it all. This show will be an exciting and informative adventure. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Award-winning pianist Kenny “Blues Boss” Wayne will be joined by Russell Jackson, the legendary bass man who played with the late, great B.B. King’s band for seven years. He has also worked with many other blues legends throughout his long career. Sherman Doucette, a local giant in the blues scene, will be playing harmonica and is a collector of vintage instruments. Joey DiMarco will round out the group, showcasing his extensive professional drumming career. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>---<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><h2>Pricing</h2><span class=\"BoldText\">Adult  $38.94</span>  ($31.50 base price + $2.36 CIF + $5.08 service charge)<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Student w/ID  $32.90</span>  ($26.25 base price + $2.36 CIF + $4.29 service charge)<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">All above prices are CAD and include GST.</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>---<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">Mary Irwin Theatre at the Rotary Centre for the Arts event tickets include a $2.36 Capital Improvement Fee (CIF). A service fee is added for box office costs, card processing, and taxes. <span class=\"BoldText\">Kenny \"Blues Boss\" Wayne</span> tickets and their applicable fees are non-refundable.</span>
""";
