<http://www.spektrix.com/kelownacommunitytheatre/event/354201ACHCPTCSRDVMDMDTRNVJTMNPKJJ>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Train Wreck Comedy - Tim Nutt & Friends";
  schema:description """
	<table class=\" BorderOn\">
		<tr>
			<td align=\"left\" colspan=\"1\"><img src=\"https://system.spektrix.com/kelownacommunitytheatre/files/8c62b1d5-495a-4fe3-98a6-25e032a928a9.jpg\" /> </td><td align=\"left\"><h2>Train Wreck Comedy presents </h2><h1><span class=\"UnderlineText\">TIM NUTT & FRIENDS</span></h1><h2><span class=\"BoldText\">Part of the Train Wreck Comedy Concert Series</span></h2><h2><span class=\"BoldText\">Presented by 104.7 The Lizard</span></h2></td>
		</tr>
	</table><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Audience advisory</span> - This event contains adult content and mature themes, and is recommended for ages 16+.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>---<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>For over 20 years, Tim Nutt has been bending, twisting, and launching comedy into entirely new dimensions.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>He doesn’t just tell jokes — he builds them. What starts as a simple story quickly spirals into explosive punchlines, razor-sharp one-liners, bizarre concepts, and brilliantly twisted observations about everyday life. His comedy sneaks up on you, builds momentum, and then hits with laugh-after-laugh precision.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Often compared to comedy greats like Billy Connolly and George Carlin, Tim is a consummate storyteller and seasoned entertainer. His ability to weave clever writing with unpredictable angles makes every performance feel fresh, dynamic, and unforgettable.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Tim has appeared at major comedy festivals around the world, including:<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>•	Just For Laughs – Montreal & Toronto<span><br/></span>•	Winnipeg Comedy Festival<span><br/></span>•	Halifax Comedy Festival<span><br/></span>•	Edinburgh Festival Fringe<span><br/></span>•	Just For Laughs National Tour<span><br/></span>•	Hubcap Comedy Festival<span><br/></span>•	Cat’s Laugh Festival (Kilkenny, Ireland)<span><br/></span>•	St. John’s Comedy Festival<span><br/></span>•	Comedy Now<span><br/></span>•	Stand Up in Kandahar (CBC)<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>From international stages to sold-out theatres across Canada, Tim Nutt continues to push comedy to explosive new levels — and this night is no exception.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>And for this special concert series event… he’s bringing friends.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Featuring:</span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Joey Commisso</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Joey Commisso brings a unique comedic perspective with a sharply off-beat delivery that has delighted audiences across Canada, the USA, and Europe. A Vancouver Comedy Award nominee and performer at JFL Vancouver, Joey’s quirky observations and unexpected punchlines make him a comedy experience you won’t forget. His ability to find humour in the sideways details of life keeps audiences leaning in — and laughing hard.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Chuck Byrn</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>With over three decades of professional stand-up experience, <span class=\"BoldText\">Chuck Byrn</span> is one of Canada’s most accomplished and road-tested comedians. He’s performed in every province and territory in the country and toured internationally, including multiple overseas tours for NATO and the Canadian Armed Forces. Chuck has appeared on Just for Laughs, Comedy Now!, The Debaters, Last Comic Standing, the Halifax Comedy Festival, and the Winnipeg Comedy Festival.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>He also spent five seasons as Head Writer for CBC’s hit series Still Standing, solidifying his reputation as both a top-tier performer and an elite comedy writer.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Having headlined major comedy clubs and theatres nationwide and featured on numerous IG Wealth Management Comedy Tours, Chuck delivers polished, high-energy comedy that connects instantly with any audience.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Tim Nutt & Friends</span> is proud to be part of the <span class=\"BoldText\">Train Wreck Comedy Concert Series</span>, produced by Train Wreck Comedy and presented by <span class=\"BoldText\">104.7 The Lizard</span> — bringing premier stand-up comedy experiences to audiences who appreciate the very best in live entertainment.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><h2>Pricing</h2><span class=\"BoldText\">Regular  $62.51</span>  ($52.00 base price + $2.36 CIF + $8.15 service charge)<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">All above prices are in CAD and include GST.</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>---<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">Mary Irwin Theatre at the Rotary Centre for the Arts event tickets include a $2.36 Capital Improvement Fee (CIF). A service fee is added for box office costs, card processing, and taxes. <span class=\"BoldText\">Train Wreck Comedy - Tim Nutt & Friends</span> tickets and their applicable fees are non-refundable.</span>
""";
